<p>This class has <em>nothing</em> to do with Drupal, it's completely our's. So you don't need
to make it extend any weird Drupal core class. <em>And</em> we can make it do whatever we
want. Create a <code>public function getRoar()</code> with a <code>$length</code> argument. Head over to
<code>RoarController</code> and copy the code that creates that. Replace <code>$count</code> with <code>$length</code>
and return that value:</p>
