<p>When I hit tab while typing the class, it auto-completes the line <em>and</em> adds the
<code>use</code> statement above the class. Do <em>not</em> forget your <code>use</code> statements people! You'll
get a "Class not found" error, and I'm pretty sure Dries gets a text message whenever
it happens. So you know, try not to make him angry: he's really tall.</p>
<p>After instantiating the <code>RoarGenerator</code> object, update the last line to
<code>$roar = $roarGenerator-&gt;getRoar();</code> and pass it <code>$count</code>:</p>
